# ─── Cowork / Claude Code local metadata ─────────────────────────
# Precautionary entries in case Cowork (or the underlying Claude
# Code agent) writes per-machine metadata into the repo folder
# during a session. As of 2026-05-11 the public Cowork docs say
# project metadata is stored separately from the context folder,
# but Claude Code conventionally drops .claude/ and CLAUDE.md
# into project roots, so ignoring those keeps the tree clean if
# Cowork ever follows the same pattern.
#
# CLAUDE.md itself is intentionally NOT ignored — if a session
# ever produces a useful project-guidance file there, we want the
# option to commit it. CLAUDE.local.md is the standard convention
# for user-specific overrides that should stay untracked.
.claude/
.cowork/
CLAUDE.local.md
